Line
best used: show the change in one or more variables over time (time-series, x-axis = time)
not ideal: have categorical data, compare multiple variables that are not dependent on time

Scatter
best used: observe relationship between two variables, ideal for showing correlation between variables,
spotting trends or outliers
not ideal: large dataset makes points overlap making it hard to interpret the data

Histogram
best used: show the distribution of a single variable. Ideal for showing frequency of data intervals.
not ideal: compare multiple variables or show the change of data over time